defaultComparing the ratio of long-haul seats flown relative to GDP of the city, Charles de Gaulle flies 81 long haul seats per million EUR of Paris GDP. Heathrow flies only 68 long haul seats per million EUR of London GDP. If Heathrow could achieve a similar seat to GDP ratio, this would imply 31 million long haul seats out of Heathrow each year instead of 26 million; an uplift of 18%”
